<p><em>Question</em></p>  <p>How can I clear namespace in an IPython notebook without clearing import statements?</p>  <hr>  <p><em>Explanation</em></p>  <p>I'm using IPython notebook similar to how someone would use Mathematica for homework. For example, to answer multiple smaller questions in a few page long document.</p>  <p>I'd like to shorten my line-count by cleaning up the import statements, since I print these assignments to physically hand-in.</p>  <hr>  <p><em>Example</em></p>  <p>1) Plot a sine function.</p>  <p><strong>In [1]</strong></p>  <pre><code>import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt %matplotlib inline  x_pts = np.arange(0, 2 * np.pi, 0.01) y_pts = np.sin(x_pts)  fig, ax = plt.subplots(1) ax.plot(x_pts, y_pts) plt.show() #plt.close(fig)  # If we forget to close something, %reset will catch our mistake. </code></pre>  <p>2) Plot a cosine function.</p>  <p><strong>In [2]</strong></p>  <pre><code>%reset -f import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt %matplotlib inline  x = np.arange(0, 2 * np.pi, 0.01) y = np.cos(x)  fig, ax = plt.subplots(1) #ax.plot(x, y_pts)  # Thanks to %reset, this line throws an error. ax.plot(x, y) plt.show() plt.close(fig)  </code></pre>  <p>This doesn't seem like a problem in a small version. However, a more-full import block gets to be pretty ugly when copy/pasted a few times.</p>  <pre><code>%reset -f %matplotlib inline import os, sys, pdb import numpy as np import sympy as sp from scipy import linalg import pandas as pd from pandas import DataFrame pd.set_option('precision', 15) np.set_printoptions(precision=15) import matplotlib.pyplot as plt from scipy import optimize, interpolate </code></pre>